  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "To set a default font in Gmail, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Gmail**: Sign in to your Gmail account.\n\n2. **Go to Settings**: Click on the gear icon (\u2699\ufe0f) in the top right corner of the Gmail interface to open the Settings menu.\n\n3. **See All Settings**: From the dropdown menu, click on \"See all settings\" to access the full settings panel.\n\n4. **Compose**: In the Settings panel, go to the \"General\" tab. This is where you can find options to customize your Gmail.\n\n5. **Default Text Style**: Look for the \"Default text style\" section. Here you can change the font style, size, and color.\n\n6. **Choose Your Font**: Click on the dropdown menus to select your preferred font, size, and other styles (bold, italic, etc.).\n\n7. **Save Changes**: After customizing your font settings, scroll to the bottom of the page and click on the \"Save Changes\" button.\n\nOnce you've set the default font, all new emails you compose will use this font until you change it again. Note that recipients may see the fonts differently depending on their email client and settings.",
